"v.使饥饿 【英】 v.使饥饿(to make or be very hungry) 【考】 反义词：surfeit(使 过饱) v. 使极度饥饿; 使饿死 【记】fa = father, mish迷失: 爸爸迷失了, 没人做饭了－使饿死(顺便说一句, 一定要学会做饭, 不然到了美国, 就等着要饭吧! )famine(n 饥荒)fa发, mine(pron 我的): 到了发我吃的地步－饥荒 【参】blemish(n 污点vt 弄脏; 玷污)布莱尔迷失了; skirmish(n 小冲突v 进行小冲突)skirt mish: 裙子丢了, 容易引起小夫妻间的小冲突. 【反】surfeit(vt 使沉溺于; 使过饱) 【记】famine；音：乏米食，乏米吃→缺米吃→饥饿 famish (v.)  c.1400, famyschen, alteration of famen (late 14c.), a shortening of Old French afamer, from Vulgar Latin *affamare ""to bring to hunger,"" from ad famem, from Latin fames ""hunger"" (see famine). Ending changed mid-14c. to -ish under influence of ravish, anguish, etc. The intransitive sense is from 1520s. Related: Famished; famishing."
